## Generic Production Example (copy & adapt per environment)

## Shared Values
NODE_ENV=production
CLIENT_URL=https://your-domain.com
SESSION_SECRET=generate-a-strong-random-secret-openssl-rand-base64-32
MONGODB_URI=replace-with-production-mongodb-uri

## Microservice Ports (may be ignored by some PaaS platforms)
AUTH_SERVICE_PORT=3001
USER_SERVICE_PORT=3002
INVOICE_SERVICE_PORT=3003
PORT=3000

## Service URLs (if using internal networking / container host)
AUTH_SERVICE_URL=http://auth-service:3001
USER_SERVICE_URL=http://user-service:3002
INVOICE_SERVICE_URL=http://invoice-service:3003

## Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=replace-google-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=replace-google-client-secret
# Redirect URI must match: https://your-domain.com/auth/google/callback

## OpenAI
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-production-openai-key-here

## Notes
# - All services must share identical SESSION_SECRET for session persistence.
# - Set secure cookies automatically via NODE_ENV=production.
# - If deploying each service separately, set CLIENT_URL consistently everywhere.
# - Remove any ports/URLs not required by your hosting provider.
